// Array-defination:
// As in simple language "array" ka mtlb hota hai ki "collection of mutiple-items of same type" , thus toh yaha computer-programming meh bhi Array ka mtlb bhi yahi hota hai bas thoda yaha items ka difference hai, mtlb yaha items hai single-variable-containers(not "Node" sirf simple-single-variable-container). so thus toh..
//"Array" is collection of single-variables-containers, and where yeh single-variabel-containers contiguous hoteh hai mtlb unke addresses- sequence meh hoteh hai jaise 204, 208 , 212 and soo..on upto size of array. and or apn orr simply esseh bhi bol skteh hai ki "Array" is a collection of variables.. , whereas-notepoint ki yeh single-varialble-container ko apn ""single-valued-container"" bhi bolteh hai and aur "scalar-variable-container" bhi bolteh hai.. as apn esko scalar essliy bol rahe hai q ki ess container meh only ek hi value hai , ek hi cheeze mtlb value k saat meh orr koi cheeze nhi hai jaise "direction" etc.. etc.. but as programming meh "pointers" hoteh hai "direction" ki jagah.. and toh mtlb jin container meh "values" and "pointers" usseh apn "Node" bolteh hai or comonly "Vector" bhi bol deteh hai. and jis container meh only "values" mtlb "values-containers" hoteh hai usko apn "Array" bolteh hai, but majorly and commanly not in terms of memory "Array" ko collection of values bol diya jata hai , but in actual Array is collection of containers where voh containers can be sclar-container or vector-container or Node etc..etc.. and yeh actual wali cheez memory-ki-terms meh define huee hai. and apn mtlb ajay as a programmer programming-concept ko dono tarah se dekhteh and define krteh hai, mtlb phle in terms of memory dekhteh , samajteh hai and then phir comman-general bhasa meh dekhteh hai and define krteh hai. and yeh dono hi bohat-bohat jaruri hai, important hai.

// note-point: as toh values nhi hoti , actual meh Containers hoteh hai . and unn Containers meh values hoti hai. as toh hamesa apnko "Containers" ki terms meh hi sari cheeze sochni hai..

